import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.scatter(data['u'], data['v'])
    ax.set_xlabel('u')
    ax.set_ylabel('v')
    plt.title('What is the correlation between u and v?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['u'].plot(kind='hist', bins=20, alpha=0.5, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['u'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['u'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['u'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['u'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of u?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):

    data = data.sort_values(by='index')
    plt.plot(data['index'], data['u'])
    plt.title('What is the relationship between index and u?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
